The paper is about search engines and their dependence on user-generated content, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions analyzing the results for different types of queries, which involves natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper touches upon the economic benefits of intelligent technologies, which could fall under the categories of Cybernetics (cs.CY) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions auditing and empirical analysis, which could fall under the category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL).
